ve been hit with scourge, finished killing Oowomp, then start bandaging myself and survived it. Of course I keep phantom chain up while I'm camping him. I found that cinder bolt works better for me instead of a rain spell because he seems to break root fairly easily. Also, if he manages to gate, the bolt will still follow him and singe his tail. I also usually pull with cinder bolt, which will unfortunately get a lot of his attention before pet can taunt him off, but lets you get in a hefty initial amount of damage from the get go. Just my 2cp worth, hope it helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udeenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/01 4:09:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Another reason to use the RAIN series is actually the most important reason to use them.<br>
<br>
As the rain does damage (providing it's not resisted), you'll have time to whip up a BOLT that should land about the time the last wave of rain hits.  If successful, you'll do over 50% with no problem and by the time your aggro is high enough that he abandons your pet to bash you in, he's dead.<br>
<br>
And another point I should have mentioned...if you have a chioce to wear INT gear vs resist gear,  go for the resist gear.  He won't need much mana, if done correctly, and the resists will help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uackar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ackar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(7/10/01 10:38:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> The pandos quest to get quick faction with the dwarves/elves has been 'fixed' by Verant when they removed muffins from most of the venders. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umurlow98.showPublicProfile?language=EN>murlow98</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(7/19/01 6:16:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Muffins are back at Pincia Brownloe's bakery. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uackar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ackar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(7/27/01 6:02:20 am)</font><br>